Guest Choral clinician was Mr. Eric Richardson. Band students of Mrs. Dana Willman-Leber were Lillian Watson, Lillian Schiefer, Madison Enders, and Myah Geary. Guest Band clinician was Mr. Jonathon Waters. Following an all-day rehearsal, the final concert included the Honors Orchestra, Choir, and Band. Congratulations to these fine musicians!

post_text:
Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays!! This is Jen👋 and I just have to share how amazing our band kids are and why I love, and care for each one like my own. My truly amazing daughter when I was first diagnosed with this illness came to the band and asked them for Christmas if they would either as a section, or individually write down encouraging words that would help me through those rough days. Let me tell you they did not disappoint. I read each one today, and there were tear, not sadness tears, but those of joy,happiness, and the fact you know that you have a whole group of kids that are behind you that believe in you and are rooting for you. On those bad days I know I will have some of the best cheer me-ups words to read. Just known I truly miss being around these kids and doing what I can for them. 💕❤🎶🎵🎼🎷📯🎺🎻🎸🥁💕❤
love you all!!
Jennie B!!
text:
Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays!! This is Jen👋 and I just have to share how amazing our band kids are and why I love, and care for each one like my own. My truly amazing daughter when I was first diagnosed with this illness came to the band and asked them for Christmas if they would either as a section, or individually write down encouraging words that would help me through those rough days. Let me tell you they did not disappoint. I read each one today, and there were tear, not sadness tears, but those of joy,happiness, and the fact you know that you have a whole group of kids that are behind you that believe in you and are rooting for you. On those bad days I know I will have some of the best cheer me-ups words to read. Just known I truly miss being around these kids and doing what I can for them. 💕❤🎶🎵🎼🎷📯🎺🎻🎸🥁💕❤
love you all!!
Jennie B!!

post_text: As many of you know, community member, friend, and Music Booster President Jennie Berrier was diagnosed with Stage 4 colon cancer. To show our support and to help her and her family, we are selling wristbands. All proceeds from sales will go directly to Jenn and her family. Wristbands are $4. We can take cash or checks. To be made out to Seneca East Music Boosters. Also we have bracelets at Smitty's Pizza that you can purchase from the Music Boosters. Thank you all for your continuing love and support for our beloved Jenn! 🐯🧡🖤🎶🎵

The SE Music Dept. will hold their annual Fall Food Fundraiser from Oct 15-28 in grades 6-12 Bands, Choirs, & Music Classes. Please see one of these students to place an order.
Students will have Cheese & Sausage, Auntie Anne’s Pretzels, Cinnabon, Little Caesar’s, Zap-A-Snack, & Otis Spunkmeyer Cookies among other products in their “Extravaganza! flyers. We hope you will be enticed to support the SE Music Dept with this sale for the General Fund to offset music supplies for our classes. Delivery will be before Thanksgiving when payments are due.
